gurmukhi: hX nkRu Dujw dRum sRauxq nIr mY ckR ijau ckR iPrY grqw ]
transliteration: Hay Nark(u) Dhujaa Droum Sraounat Noor Mai Chakra Jio Chakra Hirai Gadtaa||
translation: Within the blood of the horses, chariots and wheels of chariots are rotating as in whirlpools of water.

gurmukhi: qb suMB insuMB duhUM imil dwnv mwr krI rn mY srqw ]69]
transliteration: Tab Sounbh Nisounbh Duhoon Mil(i) Daanav Maar Daroo Ran Mai Sartaa||69||
translation: Sumbh and Nisumbh waged such a furious war together which hath caused the flow of the stream of blood in the field.69.

gurmukhi: sur hwry jIqy Asur lIny skl smwj ]
transliteration: Sur Hdare Jeete Asur Loone Sakal Samaaj||
translation: The gods were defeated and the demons were victorious who captured all the paraphernalia.

gurmukhi: dIno ieMdR Bjwie kY mhwN pRbl dl swj ]70]
transliteration: Doono Indra Bhajaae Kai Mahaan Prabal Dal Saaj||70||
translation: With the help of very powerful army, they caused the flight of Indra.70.

gurmukhi: CIn BMfwr lieE hY kubyr qy syshuM qy mn mwl CfweI ]
transliteration: Chhodhn Bhandaar Laio Hai Kouber Te Sesahoun Te Man Maal Chhadnoo||
translation: The demons seized away the wealth from Kuber and the necklace of jewels from Sheshanaga.

gurmukhi: jIq lukys idnys insys gnys jlys dIE hY BjweI ]
transliteration: Jeet Loukes Dines Nises Gades Jales Dooo Hai Bhajaaoo||
translation: They conquered Brahma, Sun, Moon, Ganesh, Varuna etc., and caused them to run away.

gurmukhi: lok kIey iqn qInhu Awpny dYq pTY qh dY TkurweI ]
transliteration: Lok Kooe Tin Toonoh Aapne Dait Padhhai Tah Dai Thakuraaoo||
translation: They established their own kingdom after conquering all the three worlds.

gurmukhi: jwie bsy sur Dwm qyaU iqn suMB insuMB kI PyrI duhweI ]71]
transliteration: Jaae Bade Sur Dhaam Teoo Tin Sounbh Nisounbh Koo Pheroo Duhaaoo||71||
translation: All the demons went to abide in the cities of gods and proclamations were made in the names of Sumbh and Nisumbh.71.

gurmukhi: Kyq jIq dYqn lIE gey dyvqy Bwj ]
transliteration: Khet Jeet Daitan Looo Gad Devate Bhaaj||
translation: The demos conquered the war the gods ran away.

gurmukhi: iehY ibcwirE mn ibKy lyhu isvw qy rwj ]72]
transliteration: Ihai Bichaario Man Bikhe Leh(u) Sivaa Te Raaj||72||
translation: The gods then ruminated in their mind that Shiva be propitiated for re-establishment of their rule.72.
